title: Roundup (Oct. 8): Joppatowne gets rare win over Harford Tech in boys soccer
text:
Roundup (Oct. 8): Joppatowne gets rare win over Harford Tech in boys soccer soccer Theo Karanikos / Associated Press From Sun staff reports 
Dylan Purkey scored the game-winner in the 69th minute to lift Joppatowne over host Harford Tech, 2-1, on Thursday in boys soccer. 
The win is the first by the Mariners (4-3) over the Cobras (3-5) in 15 years. 
Tajohn Willis gave Joppatowne a 1-0 lead five minutes into the game. Eight minutes later, Colin Dehner tied the score. 
No. 6 Perry Hall 6, Franklin 0: Jack Muller scored twice to lead the host Gators (8-2) past the Indians (1-5-2). 
No. 7 C. Milton Wright 4, Rising Sun 0: Kyle Walters scored twice to lead the host Mustangs (5-2) past the Tigers (2-3). 
Girls soccer 
No. 9 Fallston 3, Patterson Mill 0: Alicyn Lose scored twice as the Cougars (9-1) shut out the host Huskies (4-5).
